<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-765-972  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 765 972.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Oct 16 1989 v6 n41 p23(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>VAX accounting package offers pop-up windows. (MinicomputerBusiness Computer Applications' Classic)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bowen, Ted Smalley.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Minicomputer Business Applications Inc. (product enhancement).andO;Product:   Classic (Computer program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     EnhancementsFinancial SoftwareAccounting.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>VAX Accounting Package Offers Pop-Up WindowsandM;GLENDALE, Calif.andP;  -- The latest version of Minicomputer Business ComputerApplications' (MCBA's) Classic accounting, distribution and manufacturingsoftware will provide pop-up windowing for VAXes, with functions such asmultitasking, menu customizing, and on-line help, company officials said.andM;The updated version will be demonstrated at the Dexpo West trade show inAnaheim, Calif., next month.andM;Ian Dale, MCBA's vice president of operations, said the company has made&quot;functionality changes to the whole system, making it easier for first-timeusers and more efficient for experienced users.&quot;andM;Dale said the upgrade provides the &quot;ability to dive around among packages andlevels, which is not typically found on minis.&quot;andM;The upgrade adds branching and windows to Classic's transfer capabilities.andM;Project Manager John Hill said that the upgraded Classic software will offercomplete on-line help at any level, and the help line will be touch-senstive.andM;MCBA's software runs on the following systems: VAX, Wang VS,Hewlett-Packard's 3000, Unix and Xenix.andM;It also runs on PC-DOS and MS-DOS local area networks, a company officialsaid.andM;Dale said that, though the Classic software does not run on Ultrix, &quot;thereare resellers who [have ported the product].&quot;andM;MCBA has no plans to support DECwindows, he said.andM;The latest version of the Classic package is expected to be available in thefirst quarter of 1990.andM;The company has not yet announced prices.andM;For additional information about Classic software, Minicomputer BusinessComputer Applications, Inc. can be contacted at 425 W. Broadway, Glendale, CA91204, (818) 242-9600.andO;</TEXT></DOC>